    "content": "<p>Sodium ethanoate on heating with soda lime gives ' $X^{\\prime}$. Electrolysis of aqueous solution of sodium ethanoate gives ' $Y^{\\prime}$. ' $X^{\\prime}$ and ' $Y^{\\prime}$ respectively are</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": " methane and ethane\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": " methane and methane\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": " ethane and methane\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": " ethane and ethane"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>The complete reaction sequence involved is as follows</p>\n<p>$\\underset{\\text { Sodium ethanoate }}{\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{COONa}}+\\underset{\\substack{\\text { Sodium } \\\\ \\text { hydroxide }}}{\\mathrm{NaOH}} \\xrightarrow[\\Delta]{\\mathrm{CaO}} \\underset{\\substack{\\text { Methane } \\\\(X)}}{\\mathrm{CH}_4}+\\mathrm{Na}_2 \\mathrm{CO}_3$</p>\n<p>$2 \\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{COONa}+2 \\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{O} \\xrightarrow{\\Delta} \\xrightarrow[\\substack{\\text { Ethane } \\\\(Y)}]{\\mathrm{C}_2 \\mathrm{H}_6}+2 \\mathrm{NaOH} +2 \\mathrm{CO}_2+\\mathrm{H}_2$</p>\n<p>Thus, the compounds X and Y are methane and ethane respectively.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2024,
    "yearKey": "kcet-2024",
    "difficulty": null
  },
