      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>To prepare 2-methyl propane by Wurtz reaction, the haloalkanes that should be taken along with metallic sodium and dry ether are chloromethane and 2 -chloropropane. The reaction involved is</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m5wit6zn/75f9c589-8bfe-46ee-9d12-1e4e747535de/2176bf30-d27d-11ef-acf1-4d81512d7f21/file-jaoe38c1m5wit6zo.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m5wit6zn/75f9c589-8bfe-46ee-9d12-1e4e747535de/2176bf30-d27d-11ef-acf1-4d81512d7f21/file-jaoe38c1m5wit6zo.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2024 Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 7 English Explanation\"></p>",
