    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>The complete reaction sequence involved is as follows</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m5xae3ru/a324e3fb-4a9a-4d19-b8fb-1f18191830bf/fd753fa0-d2e8-11ef-8c71-155e85fd2e64/file-jaoe38c1m5xae3rv.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m5xae3ru/a324e3fb-4a9a-4d19-b8fb-1f18191830bf/fd753fa0-d2e8-11ef-8c71-155e85fd2e64/file-jaoe38c1m5xae3rv.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2024 Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 8 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>Thus, the reagent $P, Q, R$ and $S$ are $\\mathrm{Br}_2$, alc. KOH , $\\mathrm{NaNH}_2$, Red hot iron respectively.</p>",
