  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>The number of $$\\pi$$-bonds and $$\\sigma$$-bonds present in naphthalene are respectively</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "6, 19"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "5, 19"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "5, 11"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "5, 20"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "B"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Sigma ($$\\sigma$$) bonds are formed by the linear or axial or end to end overlapping of orbitals and pi $$(\\pi)$$ bonds are formed by the parallel or sidewise overlapping of orbitals by the given compound (i.e. naphthalene) number of $$\\pi$$-bonds and $$\\sigma$$-bonds are 5 and 19 respectively.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ltsnelwa/2bfc4f0f-54b4-4023-8403-a0abe28fdcc2/5e57cba0-e2c9-11ee-b28f-e16455d50713/file-1ltsnelwb.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ltsnelwa/2bfc4f0f-54b4-4023-8403-a0abe28fdcc2/5e57cba0-e2c9-11ee-b28f-e16455d50713/file-1ltsnelwb.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2019 Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 10 English Explanation\"></p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2019,
    "yearKey": "kcet-2019",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>2-butyne is reduced to trans-but-2-ene using</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "$$\\mathrm{H}_2 \\mid \\mathrm{Ni}$$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "$$\\mathrm{Na}$$ in liq. $$\\mathrm{NH}_3$$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "$$\\mathrm{H}_2 \\mid \\mathrm{Pd}-\\mathrm{C}$$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "$$\\mathrm{Zn}$$ in dil. $$\\mathrm{HCl}$$"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "B"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>2-butyne is reduced to trans but-2-ene using $$\\mathrm{Na}$$ in liq. $$\\mathrm{NH}_3$$. The reaction is as follows</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ltu11ehu/3ebd44a5-5094-4fd7-a3fa-9ba111a806d3/77907820-e38b-11ee-9a85-437c7e7ea066/file-1ltu11ehv.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ltu11ehu/3ebd44a5-5094-4fd7-a3fa-9ba111a806d3/77907820-e38b-11ee-9a85-437c7e7ea066/file-1ltu11ehv.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2019 Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 11 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>But if $$\\mathrm{H}_2 / \\mathrm{Pd}-\\mathrm{C}$$ is used then cis-but-2-ene will form. Here, partially deactivated palladised charcoal is known as Lindlar's catalyst.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2019,
    "yearKey": "kcet-2019",
    "difficulty": null
  },
