        "content": "butanal"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "C"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<ol start=\"11\">\n<p> When vapours of $3^{\\circ}$-alcohols are passed over heated copper at 573 K alkenes are formed.</p>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m7hktpt5/d5d78c6c-eda1-4a92-afcf-f1945b97f19d/af46bd90-f1dd-11ef-aab0-892656acd133/file-jaoe38c1m7hktpt6.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m7hktpt5/d5d78c6c-eda1-4a92-afcf-f1945b97f19d/af46bd90-f1dd-11ef-aab0-892656acd133/file-jaoe38c1m7hktpt6.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"KCET 2018 Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 4 English Explanation\"></ol>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2018,
    "yearKey": "kcet-2018",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "For the preparation of alkanes, aqueous solution of sodium of potassium salt of carboxylic acid is subjected to\n",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "hydrolysis\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": " electrolysis\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": " hydrogenation\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "oxidation"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "B"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>The correct answer is <strong>Option B: electrolysis</strong>. This process is known as Kolbe electrolysis.</p>\n<p>Here's why:</p>\n\n<p><p><strong>Kolbe Electrolysis:</strong> When an aqueous solution of sodium or potassium salt of a carboxylic acid is electrolyzed, it results in the formation of an alkane.</p>\n<p>$$2RCOO^-Na^+ + 2H_2O \\xrightarrow{Electrolysis} R-R + 2CO_2 + H_2 + 2NaOH$$</p>\n<p>In this reaction:</p>\n\n<p><p>The $RCOO^-$ part comes from the sodium or potassium salt of the carboxylic acid.</p></p>\n<p><p>Electrolysis involves passing an electric current through the solution.</p></p>\n<p><p>$R-R$ represents the alkane formed.</p></p></p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2017,
    "yearKey": "kcet-2017",
    "difficulty": null
  }
